{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T03:31:31.003Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 1}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss Functions in Supervised Learning"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Loss Functions — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What is a Loss Function?"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "loss function"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (also called cost function or error function) is a mathematical formula that measures "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "how wrong"}, {"type": "text", "text": " a model's predictions are compared to the actual ground truth labels. It quantifies the \"cost\" or \"penalty\" for prediction errors."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Core purpose"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": During training, the model's goal is to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "minimize"}, {"type": "text", "text": " this loss by adjusting its parameters (weights)."}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{Loss} = \\text{measure of distance between } \\hat{y} \\text{ (prediction)} \\text{ and } y \\text{ (actual)}"}}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Loss Functions Matter"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Role"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training guidance"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss tells the model which direction to update weights (via gradient descent)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Performance metric"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lower loss = better model fit on training data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Algorithm selection"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Different algorithms use different loss functions (SVM → hinge loss, logistic regression → cross-entropy)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convergence control"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Shape of loss function affects how quickly/stably model converges"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "**Key property**: Loss functions should satisfy \\( \\phi(z) \\to 0 \\) as \\( z \\to \\infty \\) (correct predictions have low loss) and \\( \\phi(z) \\to \\infty \\) as \\( z \\to -\\infty \\) (wrong predictions have high loss). [cs229.stanford](https://cs229.stanford.edu/extra-notes/loss-functions.pdf)"}}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss Functions for Regression"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Regression predicts "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "continuous values"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Loss functions measure the difference between predicted and actual numerical values."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean Squared Error (MSE / L2 Loss / Square Loss)"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{MSE} = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}(y_i - \\hat{y}_i)^2"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Most common"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for regression problems"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Squared penalty"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": larger errors contribute disproportionately more"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sensitive to outliers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (because of squaring)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Differentiable everywhere; smooth gradient"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Used in: linear regression, neural networks for regression"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean Absolute Error (MAE / L1 Loss)"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{MAE} = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}|y_i - \\hat{y}_i|"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Measures "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "average absolute difference"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small and large errors weighted equally"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Less sensitive to outliers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " than MSE"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Non-differentiable at 0"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (can cause optimization issues)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Used when: robustness to outliers is important"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Huber Loss"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{Huber} = \n\\begin{cases}\n\\frac{1}{2}(y - \\hat{y})^2 & \\text{if } |y - \\hat{y}| \\leq \\delta \\\\\n\\delta \\cdot (|y - \\hat{y}| - \\frac{1}{2}\\delta) & \\text{otherwise}\n\\end{cases}"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Combines MSE + MAE"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": uses MSE for small errors, MAE for large errors"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Less sensitive to outliers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " while remaining differentiable"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Parameterized by δ (hyperparameter controlling the threshold)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Used when: you want robustness without optimization issues"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{RMSE} = \\sqrt{\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}(y_i - \\hat{y}_i)^2}"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MSE with square root applied"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss has "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "same units as target variable"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (easier interpretation)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss Functions for Classification"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Classification predicts "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "discrete categories"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Loss functions measure dissimilarity between predicted probabilities and true class labels."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Binary Cross-Entropy (BCE / Log Loss)"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{BCE} = -\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}\\left[y_i\\log(\\hat{y}_i) + (1-y_i)\\log(1-\\hat{y}_i)\\right]"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "binary classification"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (2 classes: 0/1)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Measures "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "dissimilarity between predicted probability and true label"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Perfect model → log loss of 0"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Confident but wrong predictions penalized heavily"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (log penalty explodes as probability → 0)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Used in: logistic regression, binary neural network classifiers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cross-Entropy Loss (Multi-class)"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{CE} = -\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}\\sum_{j=1}^{k}y_{ij}\\log(\\hat{y}_{ij})"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Extension of BCE to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "k > 2 classes"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "neural network classification"}, {"type": "text", "text": " tasks"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Used in: softmax classifiers, GPT (next-token prediction), image classification"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hinge Loss"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{Hinge} = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}\\max(0, 1 - y_i\\hat{y}_i)"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Based on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "margin concept"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (distance to decision boundary)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Penalizes "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "wrong predictions"}, {"type": "text", "text": " AND "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "confident-but-wrong predictions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Primarily used for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Support Vector Machines (SVMs)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Goal: maximize margin between classes"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Zero-One Loss"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "L_{0/1} = \n\\begin{cases}\n1 & \\text{if } y_i \\neq \\hat{y}_i \\text{ (wrong)} \\\\\n0 & \\text{if } y_i = \\hat{y}_i \\text{ (correct)}\n\\end{cases}"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Simply counts "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "number of prediction errors"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not differentiable"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → can't use gradient descent"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mainly theoretical; used for accuracy evaluation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "5. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Perceptron Loss"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{Perceptron} = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}\\max(0, -y_i\\hat{y}_i)"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Penalizes wrong predictions by "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "extent of violation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss = 0 when correctly classified"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Used in: perceptron algorithm"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "6. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Exponential Loss"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{Exp} = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^{n}e^{-y_i\\hat{y}_i}"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Exponential penalty"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for wrong predictions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Used in: boosting algorithms (AdaBoost)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Very sensitive to outliers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss Function Selection Guide"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scenario"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Recommended Loss"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Regression, normal outliers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MSE"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Smooth gradients, standard choice"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Regression, heavy outliers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MAE or Huber"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Robust to extreme values"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Binary classification"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Binary Cross-Entropy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Probabilistic interpretation, standard"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multi-class classification"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Entropy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Extends BCE naturally"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SVM training"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hinge Loss"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Maximizes margin"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Boosting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Exponential Loss"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Strong penalty for errors"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Need accuracy metric"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Zero-One Loss"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Directly counts errors"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Connection to Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Understanding loss functions is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "critical for generative AI"}, {"type": "text", "text": " because:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "GPT/LLMs"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "cross-entropy loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for next-token prediction (classification over vocabulary)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Image generation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Diffusion models): Often use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "MSE"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to predict continuous pixel values or noise"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training stability"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Choice of loss affects convergence speed and final model quality"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fine-tuning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Loss function determines what the model optimizes for (e.g., accuracy vs. robustness)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mental model"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Think of loss as the \"score\" the model tries to minimize. Different tasks need different scoring rules—just like basketball and soccer have different ways to count points."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss functions measure prediction error"}, {"type": "text", "text": "; models minimize loss during training via gradient descent"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regression → MSE/MAE/Huber"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (measure continuous differences)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Classification → Cross-Entropy/Hinge"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (measure probability dissimilarity or margin)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Outlier sensitivity"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": MSE > Cross-Entropy > MAE > Huber"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Differentiability matters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Zero-one loss can't use gradient descent; MAE has issues at 0"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "generative AI"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", cross-entropy dominates (token prediction is classification)"}]}]}]}]}}